column6: Compare column D and column G to K
Column G to K are all Brand+Line
Match the front of each string to the longest version possible of Brand
The part after the Brand will be the Line
compare it to G to K column
Brand+Line match example: G8 to G13
601=parent. text AFTER "601" is the Line name and the Line is a child of "601"
With the above, we have data: Brand, Line, Brand+Line for each entry
I bolded all the Lines under the Brand "601" in column G to K, just to show the matches
Then the matches should be de-duped, just unique values for Line
The Brand+Line dasta from this sheet and cigarscanner (need to be scraped), will combine to create a comprehensive list of all Brands, and Lines under that Brand
